      • tryGet

        Object tryGet(String path)
       throws NoFieldException
        Tries to get the object associated with the specified key as name, if possible. In case that name does not refer to a value a NoFieldException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        path - the path pointing to the element to retrieve
        Returns:
        the element at the specified path
        Throws:
        NoFieldException - if the specified name does not refer to any value.

      • get

        Object get(String path,
           Object def)
        Returns the the value associated with the specified key as name, if possible. In case that name does not refer to any value the specified default value will be returned (but not stored !).
        Parameters:
        path - the name of the value to retrieve.
        def - the default value to return of none available.
        Returns:
        the value with the specified name.
